The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 November is 97,330 (11,217.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 November, there were 4,528 new confirmed cases (521.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 October, there were 4,571 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 1% (43 fewer cases).
